.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-TCCLASSES 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-tcclasses \- traffic shaping class definitions for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I tcclasses
file defines the traffic classes for the interfaces declared in
.IR shorewall\-nft\-tcdevices (5).
Each row defines a class with a guaranteed rate, a ceiling rate, and a
priority.  shorewall-nft generates
.BR tc (8)
class commands via
.BR "shorewall\-nft generate\-tc" .

Packets are assigned to classes by nft mark rules derived from
.I tcrules
and
.IR mangle .

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/tcclasses
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
INTERFACE	yes	Interface (must be declared in tcdevices)
MARK	yes	Packet mark value that identifies this class
RATE	yes	Guaranteed bandwidth (e.g. 1mbit)
CEIL	no	Maximum bandwidth / ceiling (default: interface rate)
PRIORITY	no	Class priority (1=highest; default: 1)
OPTIONS	no	Comma-separated options (default, …)
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Three priority classes on a 10 Mbit uplink:
.RS
.nf
#INTERFACE  MARK  RATE    CEIL    PRIORITY
eth0        1     5mbit   10mbit  1
eth0        2     3mbit   10mbit  2
eth0        3     1mbit   10mbit  3
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcdevices (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcfilters (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-mangle (5)

